<span id="iii.ii-p1"></span> <span class="sc"><span
id="iii.ii-p1.1"></span>Commonitory</span>. I have retained the original
title in its anglicised form, already familiar to English ears in
connection with the name of Vincentius. Its meaning as he uses it is
indicated sufficiently, in § 3, “An aid to memory.” Technically, it
meant a Paper of Instructions given to a person charged with a
commission, to assist his memory as to its details.

